China’s Sina Rises First Time in Six Days in New York Trading

-- B y   B e l i n d a   C a o
-- 
2011-06-10T14:32:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/china-s-sina-rises-first-time-in-six-days-in-new-york-trading.html
Sina Corp., owner of  China ’s third-
most visited website and the Twitter-like Weibo service, rose
for the first day in six trading sessions, paring a 27 percent
decline over the past five days.  The shares rose 2.2 percent to $92.89 at 10:29 a.m. New
York time.  The shares recent retreat have created a buying
opportunity, analysts at Piper Jaffray Cos. including  Gene
Munster  wrote in a research note today. He maintains an
“overweight” rating on Sina and a price target of $139.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Belinda Cao in New York at 
 lcao4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
